reviewText: Couldn't even watch the whole movie it was so bad and it is less than 1 star.

I don't really know who the writer of this film is, but I really enjoyed the structured story line of this film. The cast seemed to balance each other out, not to mention that the receptionist is a freaking knockout...... I have one word for her ROARRRRRRRRRRRR
This movie was very impressive and I would deffinetly recommend it to anyone who wants to be entertained and enjoy what they are watching.

This movie has a little something for everything, to entertain and offend! Reminiscent of the great 80s trash camp flicks. Grab a case of beer and a bucket of chicken and you have a fun night in with your movie watching buddies.

And very quotable too! "Are you on...THE POT?!?" Stoner buddies will think this is a hoot.
Writer Barry Ratcliffe's  imaginative, campy script mixes horror with humor.  Low budget but high talent version of the sotry of Pocahauntus' revenge.  A showcase for up and coming stars!
